WEBVTT

1
00:00:12.785 --> 00:00:15.327
I could never have imagined
我永远都不会想象到

2
00:00:15.351 --> 00:00:19.303
that a 19-year-old suicide bomber
一个19岁的自杀式炸弹袭击者

3
00:00:19.327 --> 00:00:23.008
would actually teach me a valuable lesson.
会给我上了珍贵的一堂课

4
00:00:24.460 --> 00:00:25.627
But he did.
但这就是事实

5
00:00:26.460 --> 00:00:34.243
He taught me to never presume anything about anyone you don't know.
他教会了我，永远不要对陌生人先入为主地妄下结论

6
00:00:36.234 --> 00:00:40.363
On a Thursday morning in July 2005,
那是2005年7月，一个周四早晨

7
00:00:40.387 --> 00:00:43.445
the bomber and I, unknowingly,
我并不知道自己与这位袭击者同时

8
00:00:43.469 --> 00:00:48.016
boarded the same train carriage at the same time,
上了同一节地铁车厢，

9
00:00:48.040 --> 00:00:52.503
standing, apparently, just feet apart.
我们站得很近，也就几英尺远

10
00:00:54.165 --> 00:00:55.315
I didn't see him.
我没注意他

11
00:00:56.005 --> 00:00:57.796
Actually, I didn't see anyone.
实际上，我没有注意任何人

12
00:00:57.820 --> 00:01:00.407
You know not to look at anyone on the Tube,
人们在地铁上一般不会注意任何人

13
00:01:00.431 --> 00:01:03.732
but I guess he saw me.
但我想他看见我了

14
00:01:04.736 --> 00:01:07.777
I guess he looked at all of us,
我想当时他正看着我们所有人

15
00:01:08.507 --> 00:01:12.721
as his hand hovered over the detonation switch.
手在炸弹开关上犹豫不定地徘徊

16
00:01:14.259 --> 00:01:18.704
I've often wondered: What was he thinking?
之后我经常在想：他当时在想些什么？

17
00:01:18.728 --> 00:01:22.085
Especially in those final seconds.
尤其在（爆炸前）最后几秒

18
00:01:24.585 --> 00:01:26.194
I know it wasn't personal.
我知道他并不是针对我的

19
00:01:26.797 --> 00:01:30.814
He didn't set out to kill or maim me, Gill Hicks.
他并不是要去杀掉或伤害我——吉尔•希克斯

20
00:01:30.838 --> 00:01:32.591
I mean -- he didn't know me.
因为他根本就不认识我

21
00:01:33.578 --> 00:01:34.752
No.
不认识

22
00:01:35.486 --> 00:01:43.061
Instead, he gave me an unwarranted and an unwanted label.
反之，他给我贴了一个莫须有的，可怕的标签

23
00:01:44.092 --> 00:01:47.472
I had become the enemy.
我成了敌人

24
00:01:49.210 --> 00:01:52.786
To him, I was the "other,"
于他而言，我只算是“别人”

25
00:01:52.810 --> 00:01:55.507
the "them," as opposed to "us."
与“我们”不同的“他们”

26
00:01:57.401 --> 00:02:02.675
The label "enemy" allowed him to dehumanize us.
这个“敌人”的标签允许他把我们全都非人化

27
00:02:03.494 --> 00:02:05.921
It allowed him to push that button.
也允许了他去按下那个按钮

28
00:02:07.159 --> 00:02:09.326
And he wasn't selective.
我们并不是某个特定的目标

29
00:02:10.695 --> 00:02:15.878
Twenty-six precious lives were taken in my carriage alone,
仅仅是我所在的那一个车厢，26个宝贵的生命消逝了

30
00:02:16.862 --> 00:02:18.790
and I was almost one of them.
我也几乎成为了其中的一员

31
00:02:20.675 --> 00:02:23.416
In the time it takes to draw a breath,
在一个深呼吸所需的瞬间

32
00:02:23.440 --> 00:02:27.110
we were plunged into a darkness so immense
我们坠入了一片无边无际的黑暗

33
00:02:27.134 --> 00:02:29.516
that it was almost tangible;
那黑暗几乎触手可及

34
00:02:29.540 --> 00:02:33.899
what I imagine wading through tar might be like.
或许蹚过柏油的感觉也不过如此

35
00:02:35.218 --> 00:02:37.268
We didn't know we were the enemy.
我们不知道我们被划成了“敌人”

36
00:02:38.141 --> 00:02:42.199
We were just a bunch of commuters who, minutes earlier,
我们只是一群上班族，几分钟前

37
00:02:42.223 --> 00:02:44.707
had followed the Tube etiquette:
甚至还在遵守地铁乘客礼仪

38
00:02:44.731 --> 00:02:46.937
no direct eye contact,
不跟别人有直接的眼神接触

39
00:02:46.961 --> 00:02:48.111
no talking
不讲话

40
00:02:48.714 --> 00:02:51.586
and absolutely no conversation.
当然也没有任何交谈

41
00:02:53.768 --> 00:02:56.721
But in the lifting of the darkness,
但在那一片黑暗之中

42
00:02:57.596 --> 00:02:59.221
we were reaching out.
我们伸出了手

43
00:02:59.999 --> 00:03:01.511
We were helping each other.
我们在帮助彼此

44
00:03:02.628 --> 00:03:05.089
We were calling out our names,
我们叫出了各自的姓名

45
00:03:05.113 --> 00:03:07.264
a little bit like a roll call,
有点像点名那样

46
00:03:08.209 --> 00:03:10.486
waiting for responses.
等待着应答

47
00:03:12.379 --> 00:03:15.042
"I'm Gill. I'm here.
“我是吉尔。我在这儿。

48
00:03:16.931 --> 00:03:18.241
I'm alive.
我还活着

49
00:03:20.099 --> 00:03:21.288
OK."
（对方）好的。”

50
00:03:23.517 --> 00:03:24.703
"I'm Gill.
“我是吉尔。

51
00:03:25.499 --> 00:03:26.695
Here.
在这儿。

52
00:03:28.138 --> 00:03:29.447
Alive.
还活着。

53
00:03:31.149 --> 00:03:32.344
OK."
（对方）好。”

54
00:03:34.916 --> 00:03:37.457
I didn't know Alison.
我不认识艾莉森

55
00:03:38.219 --> 00:03:42.461
But I listened for her check-ins every few minutes.
但我每隔几分钟 就期待着她的报到

56
00:03:43.160 --> 00:03:44.778
I didn't know Richard.
我也不认识理查德

57
00:03:45.659 --> 00:03:48.548
But it mattered to me that he survived.
但他活下来了，这对我意义重大

58
00:03:50.572 --> 00:03:52.366
All I shared with them
我和他们分享的所有

59
00:03:52.390 --> 00:03:53.873
was my first name.
仅仅是我的名字而已（并不是全名）

60
00:03:54.833 --> 00:03:55.984
They didn't know
他们不知道

61
00:03:55.808 --> 00:03:59.531
that I was a head of a department at the Design Council.
我是英国设计理事会的 一个部门主管

62
00:04:01.005 --> 00:04:04.562
And here is my beloved briefcase,
我带着我心爱的行李箱

63
00:04:04.586 --> 00:04:07.037
also rescued from that morning.
那天早上它也被解救了出来

64
00:04:08.299 --> 00:04:12.265
They didn't know that I published architecture and design journals,
他们不知道我出版了建筑设计的期刊

65
00:04:12.289 --> 00:04:15.605
that I was a Fellow of the Royal Society of Arts,
也不知道我是皇家艺术协会的会员

66
00:04:15.629 --> 00:04:17.094
that I wore black --
不知道我穿的是黑衣服——

67
00:04:18.515 --> 00:04:19.681
still do --
现在也穿着——

68
00:04:20.386 --> 00:04:22.942
that I smoked cigarillos.
他们不知道我抽雪茄

69
00:04:23.708 --> 00:04:26.011
I don't smoke cigarillos anymore.
现在已经不抽了

70
00:04:25.995 --> 00:04:30.219
I drank gin and I watched TED Talks,
我喝杜松子酒，看TED演讲

71
00:04:30.243 --> 00:04:36.449
of course, never dreaming that one day I would be standing,
当然，当时我也不敢想象我有一天也会站在这儿

72
00:04:37.413 --> 00:04:40.308
balancing on prosthetic legs,
用义肢保持着平衡

73
00:04:40.332 --> 00:04:41.489
giving a talk.
发表演讲

74
00:04:42.471 --> 00:04:48.115
I was a young Australian woman doing extraordinary things in London.
我是个年轻的澳大利亚女人，在伦敦做着不可思议的工作

75
00:04:48.139 --> 00:04:50.972
And I wasn't ready for that all to end.
我还没准备好结束那一切

76
00:04:52.702 --> 00:04:55.860
I was so determined to survive
我迫切地想要活下来

77
00:04:55.884 --> 00:05:01.086
that I used my scarf to tie tourniquets around the tops of my legs,
我用围巾充当止血带，把它缠绕在大腿上

78
00:05:01.110 --> 00:05:06.443
and I just shut everything and everyone out,
我把所有人，所有事都给屏蔽掉了

79
00:05:07.165 --> 00:05:10.425
to focus, to listen to myself,
只是专注地倾听自己

80
00:05:10.449 --> 00:05:13.583
to be guided by instinct alone.
只接受本能的引导

81
00:05:14.905 --> 00:05:16.999
I lowered my breathing rate.
我放慢呼吸速度

82
00:05:17.667 --> 00:05:19.447
I elevated my thighs.
把腿抬起来

83
00:05:19.471 --> 00:05:21.139
I held myself upright
我直起身

84
00:05:21.163 --> 00:05:24.833
and I fought the urge to close my eyes.
尽全力不闭上眼

85
00:05:26.501 --> 00:05:29.833
I held on for almost an hour,
我坚持了几乎一小时

86
00:05:30.850 --> 00:05:37.051
an hour to contemplate the whole of my life up until this point.
用这一个小时来思考了到那天为止的一整个人生

87
00:05:39.019 --> 00:05:42.098
Perhaps I should have done more.
也许我本应该做更多的事

88
00:05:43.043 --> 00:05:46.247
Perhaps I could have lived more, seen more.
或许我本可以经历更多事，开拓更多的视野

89
00:05:46.271 --> 00:05:50.685
Maybe I should have gone running, dancing, taken up yoga.
也许我早就该去跑步，跳舞，练瑜伽

90
00:05:52.137 --> 00:05:57.075
But my priority and my focus was always my work.
但我的焦点和重心永远是我的工作

91
00:05:57.099 --> 00:05:59.000
I lived to work.
我活着就是为了工作

92
00:05:59.550 --> 00:06:02.357
Who I was on my business card
在名片上我是什么样的

93
00:06:02.381 --> 00:06:03.651
mattered to me.
这对我很重要

94
00:06:05.508 --> 00:06:09.118
But it didn't matter down in that tunnel.
但在那个地铁隧道里这一切都不重要了

95
00:06:11.046 --> 00:06:15.516
By the time I felt that first touch
当我感觉到来自一个搜救员的

96
00:06:15.540 --> 00:06:17.680
from one of my rescuers,
第一次触碰时

97
00:06:18.292 --> 00:06:20.409
I was unable to speak,
我什么都说不出来

98
00:06:20.433 --> 00:06:25.412
unable to say even a small word, like "Gill."
甚至说不出来 一个小小的单词，比如“吉尔”

99
00:06:27.003 --> 00:06:29.738
I surrendered my body to them.
我把我自己交给了他们

100
00:06:29.762 --> 00:06:32.635
I had done all I possibly could,
我做了一切能做的

101
00:06:32.659 --> 00:06:36.355
and now I was in their hands.
此刻我把自己的生命交给了他们

102
00:06:38.911 --> 00:06:40.299
I understood
当我被送进医院时

103
00:06:41.103 --> 00:06:47.301
just who and what humanity really is,
有个身份标签一直伴随着我

104
00:06:47.792 --> 00:06:50.991
when I first saw the ID tag
当我第一次看见那个标签时

105
00:06:50.975 --> 00:06:54.268
that was given to me when I was admitted to hospital.
我理解了到底什么是真正的人性

106
00:06:54.298 --> 00:06:55.472
And it read:
那上面写着：

107
00:06:56.038 --> 00:07:01.308
"One unknown estimated female."
“一个身份不明的女性"

108
00:07:02.982 --> 00:07:07.197
One unknown estimated female.
一个身份不明的女性

109
00:07:08.824 --> 00:07:11.771
Those four words were my gift.
这些词是赠予我的礼物

110
00:07:12.945 --> 00:07:15.692
What they told me very clearly
它们清楚地告诉了我

111
00:07:15.716 --> 00:07:18.421
was that my life was saved,
我的生命被挽救

112
00:07:18.445 --> 00:07:21.589
purely because I was a human being.
仅仅是因为我是个人

113
00:07:22.430 --> 00:07:26.614
Difference of any kind made no difference
人与人之间没有任何差别

114
00:07:26.638 --> 00:07:31.195
to the extraordinary lengths that the rescuers were prepared to go
救援人员为了救我的命

115
00:07:31.949 --> 00:07:33.489
to save my life,
为了救更多的人

116
00:07:34.278 --> 00:07:37.001
to save as many unknowns as they could,
他们准备好迎接超乎寻常的跋涉

117
00:07:37.025 --> 00:07:39.357
and putting their own lives at risk.
将自己的生命置于危险之中

118
00:07:40.225 --> 00:07:44.396
To them, it didn't matter if I was rich or poor,
对他们来说，我富有或是贫穷

119
00:07:45.118 --> 00:07:47.259
the color of my skin,
我皮肤的颜色

120
00:07:47.283 --> 00:07:48.845
whether I was male or female,
我是男是女

121
00:07:48.869 --> 00:07:50.766
my sexual orientation,
我的性取向

122
00:07:51.433 --> 00:07:53.036
who I voted for,
为谁投了票

123
00:07:52.990 --> 00:07:54.532
whether I was educated,
我是否受过教育

124
00:07:54.602 --> 00:07:58.291
if I had a faith or no faith at all.
我是否有信仰，这些都不重要

125
00:07:59.229 --> 00:08:01.173
Nothing mattered
什么都不重要

126
00:08:01.197 --> 00:08:05.840
other than I was a precious human life.
除了，我代表着一个珍贵的生命

127
00:08:07.701 --> 00:08:11.181
I see myself as a living fact.
我见证了自己作为一个生命体

128
00:08:12.043 --> 00:08:14.072
I am proof
我的亲身经历证明了

129
00:08:14.096 --> 00:08:20.824
that unconditional love and respect can not only save,
无条件的爱与尊重不只能拯救生命

130
00:08:20.848 --> 00:08:23.889
but it can transform lives.
更能改变生命

131
00:08:25.046 --> 00:08:29.514
Here is a wonderful image of one of my rescuers, Andy, and I
这是一张去年拍摄的让我印象深刻的照片，是救助我的人之一，

132
00:08:29.538 --> 00:08:31.410
taken just last year.
安迪，还有我

133
00:08:31.900 --> 00:08:34.461
Ten years after the event,
事件发生十年后

134
00:08:34.485 --> 00:08:36.829
and here we are, arm in arm.
我们仍在这儿，肩并肩

135
00:08:39.379 --> 00:08:41.497
Throughout all the chaos,
穿过那一切的混乱

136
00:08:41.521 --> 00:08:44.361
my hand was held tightly.
我的手被紧握着

137
00:08:45.020 --> 00:08:47.893
My face was stroked gently.
我的脸被轻抚

138
00:08:48.981 --> 00:08:50.393
What did I feel?
我感受到了什么？

139
00:08:51.361 --> 00:08:52.583
I felt loved.
我感到被爱着

140
00:08:53.505 --> 00:08:58.322
What's shielded me from hatred and wanting retribution,
是什么让我放弃仇恨，放弃复仇

141
00:08:58.346 --> 00:09:01.335
what's given me the courage to say:
给予我勇气说出：

142
00:09:01.359 --> 00:09:04.239
this ends with me
最终我得到的

143
00:09:05.826 --> 00:09:07.017
is love.
只有爱

144
00:09:08.405 --> 00:09:10.403
I was loved.
我被爱着

145
00:09:13.054 --> 00:09:20.923
I believe the potential for widespread positive change is absolutely enormous
我相信，正能量的传播潜力是巨大的

146
00:09:20.947 --> 00:09:23.851
because I know what we're capable of.
因为我知道我们能做什么

147
00:09:23.875 --> 00:09:27.072
I know the brilliance of humanity.
我了解人类的智慧

148
00:09:27.750 --> 00:09:31.660
So this leaves me with some pretty big things to ponder
这给了我一些需要思考的东西

149
00:09:31.684 --> 00:09:35.086
and some questions for us all to consider:
以及一些我们都应反思的问题：

150
00:09:36.332 --> 00:09:42.205
Is what unites us not far greater than what can ever divide?
我们大家团结在一起的力量难道不比能摧毁我们的大许多吗？

151
00:09:43.483 --> 00:09:47.273
Does it have to take a tragedy or a disaster
是不是只有在悲剧或灾难中

152
00:09:47.297 --> 00:09:54.581
for us to feel deeply connected as one species, as human beings?
我们才能感到彼此间作为同一个物种，作为人的那种惺惺相惜？

153
00:09:55.575 --> 00:10:00.781
And when will we embrace the wisdom of our era
我们何时才能拥抱属于我们这个时代的智慧

154
00:10:01.584 --> 00:10:04.954
to rise above mere tolerance
何时才能超越单纯的宽容

155
00:10:05.751 --> 00:10:08.688
and move to an acceptance
从而升华至一种接受

156
00:10:08.712 --> 00:10:14.045
for all who are only a label until we know them?
去接受那些在我们了解他们之前，都还仅仅是一个标签的人？

157
00:10:15.370 --> 00:10:16.530
Thank you.
谢谢大家。

158
00:10:16.554 --> 00:10:23.352
(Applause)
（掌声）